OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1782290901
OL,3,CInspectors will visit Iran's nuclear
OL,4,Csites, UN says, despite mixed messaging
OL,6,FA spokesperson for Iran's Foreign
OL,7,FMinistry then rejected those comments
OL,8,Fa day later, telling reporters in
OL,9,FTehran that UN inspectors were not
OL,10,Fscheduled to examine nuclear sites
OL,11,Fbombed by the US last year.
OL,13,FPresident Donald Trump then told
OL,14,Freporters that if Iran had not agreed
OL,15,Fto inspections, he would cut off talks
OL,16,Fwith Tehran immediately. But he added
OL,17,Fthere was no rush for those
OL,18,Finspections to begin.
OL,20,FA key part of the deal
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
